text: Leticia Lee See-yin (, 17 August 1964 â€“ 16 December 2020) was a Hong Kong political activist. She was pro-China. Lee ran unsuccessfully in the 2016 Hong Kong legislative election. In 2018, Lee was accused of corruption. She had conservative views and her views of anti-LGBT rights made her controversial. Lee died on 16 December 2020 at a Hong Kong hospital at the age of 56. She tested positive for COVID-19 in the simple test before she died but it's still not confirmed that she died from COVID-19. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Hong Kong activists Category:20th-century Chinese politicians Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic
